# GlassyGaia Theme & Icon Rules

## Color usage

- **All new UI colors must come from** `src/styles/theme-colors.css` via CSS variables.
- **When introducing a new color**:
  - Declare light/dark tokens in `:root` (e.g. `--light-setlevel-text`, `--dark-setlevel-text`).
  - Map them into semantic variables inside `.light` / `.dark` (e.g. `--setlevel-text`, `--setlevel-bg`).
- **Do not hard-code hex colors** directly in components or CSS outside `theme-colors.css`.

## Typography

- Prefer existing typography utilities in `src/styles/typography.css` (e.g. `typography-pressstart-*`, `typography-inter-*`).
- New navbar buttons should generally use **Press Start 2P** to match the pixel aesthetic.

## Icons and filters

- SVG icons used via `<img src=\"...svg\" />` **must be tinted using CSS filters**, not inline `fill` attributes.
- Filters must reference dynamic variables from the `/* Icon Filter Values */` section of `theme-colors.css`:
  - Example: `filter: var(--icon-primary-filter);`, `filter: var(--icon-hover-select-filter);`.
- When a new icon color is needed (e.g. a new brand color):
  - Add light/dark filter values in `:root` (e.g. `--light-some-icon-filter`, `--dark-some-icon-filter`).
  - Map them into `.light` / `.dark` as a semantic `--icon-some-filter` variable.

## Component examples

- **Search buttons (`SearchBar` and `ContentSelector`)**
  - Button background uses `var(--primary)`.
  - Text (when present) uses `var(--hover-select)`.
  - Search icons are tinted with `filter: var(--icon-hover-select-filter);`.
  - Input borders are thin (`0.8px`) and use theme neutrals: `border: 0.8px solid var(--neutral);`.

- **Navbar `Set Level` button**
  - Uses semantic variables from `theme-colors.css`:
    - Text and border: `color: var(--setlevel-text); border-color: var(--setlevel-text);`
    - Background: `background-color: var(--setlevel-bg);`
  - The gear icon is tinted with an icon filter variable (e.g. `filter: var(--icon-primary-filter);`), not a hard-coded filter.

- **Practice button on SearchPage**
  - Background `var(--primary)`, label text `var(--hover-select)`.
  - Monster icon uses `filter: var(--icon-hover-select-filter);`.
  - Divider and chevron also use `var(--hover-select)` via theme variables.

These rules should be followed for any future navbar/search-related UI so that light/dark themes stay consistent and easy to maintain.

